casebody.data:
ROBERT E. DINEEN, SUPERINTENDENT, AS LIQUIDATOR OF NEW YORK INDEMNITY COMPANY, PETITIONER, v. THE UNITED STATES [No. 46208] [109 C. Cls. 18; 333 U. S. 842;

334 U. S. —]

Government contract; liquidated damages where suspension order was issued and contract was not terminated for delay. Petition dismissed.

Plaintiff’s petition for writ of certiorari denied by the Supreme Court March 8,1948.

Motion for leave to file petition for rehearing granted. Petition for rehearing denied May 10,1948.
